madsrdf:elementList.@comment:
The madsrdf:elementList property is used to organize the various
      parts of labels.

madsrdf:fullerName.@comment:
Full form of name needed to
      distinguish a person from another person with the same preferred name.

madsrdf:hasChararacteristic.@comment: A term that specifies a characteristic that differentiates a work or expression from another one.

madsrdf:hasIdentifier.@comment:
Associates a resource with
      a madsrdf:Identifier.

madsrdf:hasSource.@comment: Associates a resource description with its Source.

madsrdf:workOrigin.@comment: The country or other territorial jurisdiction from which a work originated.

bf:adminMetadata.@comment:
Metadata about the metadata, especially provenance information.
Used with Unspecified
should this be an annotation property? SES

bf:agent.@comment:
Entity associated with a resource or element of description, such as the name of the entity responsible for the content or of the publication, printing, distribution, issue, release or production of a resource.
Used with Unspecified
What *precisely* is an element of description? (SES)

bf:identifiedBy.@comment:
Character string associated with a resource that serves to differentiate that resource from other resources, i.e., that uniquely identifies an entity.
Used with Unspecified

bf:identifies.@comment: Resource that is associated with a character string that serves to differentiate one resource from another.

bf:language.@comment:
Language associated with a resource or its parts.
Used with Unspecified

bf:note.@comment:
General textual information relating to a resource, such as Information about a specific copy of a resource or information about a particular attribute of a resource.
Used with Unspecified

bf:place.@comment:
Geographic location or place entity associated with a resource or element of description, such as the place associated with the publication, printing, distribution, issue, release or production of a resource, place of an event.
Used with Unspecified

bf:source.@comment:
Resource from which value or label came or was derived, such as the formal source/scheme from which a classification number is taken or derived, list from which an agent name is taken or derived, source within which an identifier is unique.
Used with Unspecified
What is meant by value or label here? (SES)

bf:status.@comment:
Designation of the validity or position of something, such as indication that the classification number is canceled or invalid, circulation availability of an item, indication of whether the identifier is canceled or invalid.
Meaning is almost unspecified too. (SES)
Used with Unspecified

bf:unit.@comment:
Units in which a value is expressed, such as the physical or logical constituent of a resource (e.g., a volume, audiocassette, film reel, a map, a digital file).
Used with Unspecified
Where are these values? What are these values? (SES)

madsrdf:creationDateEnd.@comment: Ending date of the date range for which the beginning date is recorded in madsrdf:creationDateStart.

madsrdf:creationDateStart.@comment: For a work, earliest date (normally the year) associated with a work; that date may be the date the work was created or first published or released. For an expression, the earliest date (normally the year) associated with an expression; that date may be the date of the earliest known manifestation of that expression. In both cases the date may be the starting date of a range or a single date.

bf:code.@comment:
String of characters that serves as a code representing information.
Used with Unspecified

bf:count.@comment:
Number associated with a measure of units, such as the number of units and/or subunits making up a resource.
Shouldn't the number of units be some number type? (SES)
Used with Unspecified

bf:date.@comment:
Date designation associated with a resource or element of description, such as date of title variation; year a degree was awarded; date associated with the publication, printing, distribution, issue, release or production of a resource. May be date typed.
Used with Unspecified
date *may* be date typed? (ses)

bf:part.@comment:
Part of a resource to which information applies.
Used with Unspecified
What does this property do? It seems like resource is used elsewhere to refer to  some of subset of Work , Instance and Item?  But this is a data property. What information? (SES)

bf:qualifier.@comment:
Qualifier of information, such as an addition to a title to make it unique or qualifying information associated with an identifier.
Used with Unspecified
Void for vagueness. Domain Thing, Range Literal, meaning: some sort of extra information associated with some other information? (SES)

madsrdf:extendedAddress.@comment:
The second address line, if
      needed.

madsrdf:streetAddress.@comment:
First line of address. For
      second line, use madsrdf:extendedAddress.

madsrdf:hasAffiliationAddress.@comment:
The address of the group or
      organization with which an individual is associated.

madsrdf:affiliationEnd.@comment:
The date an individual
      ceased to be affiliated with an organization.

madsrdf:affiliationStart.@comment:
The date an individual
      established an affiliation with an organization.

madsrdf:hasBroaderExternalAuthority.@comment:
Creates a direct
      relationship between an Authority and a more broadly defined Authority from a different MADS
      Scheme.

madsrdf:hasCloseExternalAuthority.@comment:
Records a relationship
      between an Authority and one that is closely related from a different MADS
      Scheme.

madsrdf:hasExactExternalAuthority.@comment:
Records a relationship
      between an Authority and one to which it matches exactly but from a different MADS
      Scheme.

madsrdf:hasHiddenVariant.@comment:
Use for variants that are searchable, but not necessarily for
      display.

madsrdf:hasNarrowerAuthority.@comment:
Creates a direct
      relationship between an Authority and one that is more narrowly defined.

madsrdf:hasNarrowerExternalAuthority.@comment:
Creates a direct
      relationship between an Authority and a more narrowly defined Authority from a different MADS
      Scheme.

madsrdf:hasReciprocalAuthority.@comment:
Establishes a relationship between two Authority resources. It is
      reciprocal, so the relationship must be shared. This is Related type='equivalent' in MADS
      XML.

madsrdf:hasReciprocalExternalAuthority.@comment:
Establishes a relationship
      between an Authority and one from a different MADS Scheme. It is reciprocal, so the
      relationship must be shared.

madsrdf:hasRelatedAuthority.@comment:
Unless the relationship can be more specifically identified, use
      'hasRelatedAuthority.'

madsrdf:hasTranslationVariant.@comment:
A Variant whose label
      represents a translation of that of the authoritative label.

madsrdf:hasVariant.@comment:
Associates a Variant with an Authority or Deprecrated Authority.
      Unless the variant type can be more specifically identified, use 'hasVariant.'

madsrdf:identifiesRWO.@comment:
Associates a
      madsrdf:Authority with the Real World Object that is the subject of the authority's
      label.

madsrdf:componentList.@comment:
madsrdf:componentList
      organizes the madsrdf:SimpleType resources whose labels are represented in the label of the
      associated madsrdf:ComplexType resource.

madsrdf:hasCorporateParentAuthority.@comment:
Establishes a relationship
      between a CorporateName Authority and one of the same that is more broadly
      defined.

madsrdf:hasCorporateSubsidiaryAuthority.@comment:
Establishes a relationship
      between a CorporateName Authority and one of the same that is more narrowly
      defined.

madsrdf:idValue.@comment:
The value of the identifier
      conforming to the Identifier Scheme syntax.

madsrdf:hasMADSCollectionMember.@comment:
Associates an Authority or other Collection with a
      madsrdf:MADSCollection.

madsrdf:hasMADSSchemeMember.@comment:
Associates an Authority or Collection with a
      madsrdf:MADSScheme.

madsrdf:hasTopMemberOfMADSScheme.@comment:
Identifies an Authority
      that is at the top of the hierarchy of authorities within the MADS Scheme.
madsrdf:hasTopMemberOfMADSScheme.@label:
Has Top Member of MADS
      Scheme

madsrdf:associatedLanguage.@comment:
Language that a person,
      organization, or family uses for publication, communication, etc., or in which a work is
      expressed.

madsrdf:associatedLocale.@comment:
A town, city, province,
      state, and/or country associated with persons, corporate bodies, families, works, and
      expressions.

madsrdf:authoritativeLabel.@comment: A lexical string representing a controlled, curated label for the Authority.

madsrdf:birthPlace.@comment:
The town, city, province,
      state, and/or country in which a person was born.

madsrdf:deathPlace.@comment:
The town, city, province,
      state, and/or country in which a person died.

madsrdf:fieldOfActivity.@comment:
The field of activity
      associated with an individual.

madsrdf:hasAffiliation.@comment:
Property to associate an
      individual, such as a foaf:Agent, to a group or organization with which an individual is or
      has been affiliated.

madsrdf:isIdentifiedByAuthority.@comment:
Associates a Real World
      Object with its Authority description.

madsrdf:occupation.@comment:
A profession or occupation
      in which the person works or has worked.

madsrdf:activityEndDate.@comment: Latest date in a period of activity.

madsrdf:activityStartDate.@comment: Earliest date in a period of activity.

madsrdf:birthDate.@comment:
The year a person was born.
      Date of birth may also include the month and day of the person’s birth. (RDA
      9.3.2.1)

madsrdf:deathDate.@comment:
The year a person died.
      Date of death may also include the month and day of the person’s death. (RDA
      9.3.3.1)

madsrdf:entityDescriptor.@comment:
Any attribute that serves
      to characterize a person, family or corporate body or that may be needed for differentiation
      from other persons. families or corporate bodies and for which separate content designation is
      not already defined.Or

madsrdf:establishDate.@comment: The year a corporate body was established. Date of establishment may also include the month and day of the corporate body’s establishment.

madsrdf:gender.@comment: The gender with which a person identifies.

madsrdf:honoraryTitle.@comment:
Designation indicative of
      royalty, nobility, or ecclesiastical rank or office, or a term of address for a person of
      religious vocation.

madsrdf:prominentFamilyMember.@comment:
A well-known individual who
      is a member of the family.

madsrdf:terminateDate.@comment: The year a corporate body was terminated. Date of termination may also include the month and day of the corporate body’s termination.

madsrdf:citationStatus.@comment:
Should use a standard term - such as 'found' or 'not found' - to
      indicate whether the cited resource yielded information about the resource related to the
      madsrdf:Source.

madsrdf:hiddenLabel.@comment:
A label entered for
      discovery purposes but not shown.

madsrdf:variantLabel.@comment:
The lexical, variant form
      of an authoritative label.

@documentation.@description: Title as abbreviated for citation, indexing, and/or identification.
Access restrictions and allowances regarding access to a resource, e.g., lending policy, access restrictions, embargos.
Information about an organization, person, etc., from which a resource may be obtained.
Metadata about the metadata, especially provenance information.

bf:assigner.@comment: Entity that assigned the metadata, such as the entity that assigned a classification number, entity that assigned a name, entity that assigned an identifier.

bf:descriptionAuthentication.@comment: Indication of specific types of reviews that have been carried out on the description information.

bf:descriptionConventions.@comment: Rules used for the descriptive content of the resource description.

bf:generationProcess.@comment: Indication of the program or process used to generate the description by application of a particular transformation.

bflc:encodingLevel.@comment: Designation of the fullness of the bibliographic description.

bflc:metadataLicensor.@comment: Organization that licenses the intellectual property rights to the data contained in the description.

bf:changeDate.@comment: Date or date and time on which the metadata was modified.

bf:creationDate.@comment: Date or date and time on which the original metadata first created.

bf:derivedFrom.@comment: Link to the metadata that was the source of the data.

bf:generationDate.@comment: Date of conversion of the metadata from another format.

bflc:catalogerId.@comment: ID of the cataloger who created or edited the description.

bflc:procInfo.@comment: System-supplied processing information for the BIBFRAME description (e.g. "ibc update").

bflc:profile.@comment: Name of the BIBFRAME editor profile used to create or edit the description.

@documentation.@description: Entity having a role in a resource, such as a person or organization.
American National Standards Institute identifier.
Physical or chemical substance applied to a base material of a resource.
Resources organically created, accumulated, and/or used by a person, family, or organization in the course of conduct of affairs and preserved because of their continuing value.

Information about the organization and arrangement of a collection of items. For instance, for computer files, organization and arrangement information may be the file structure and sort sequence of a file; for visual materials, this information may be how a collection is arranged.

bf:hierarchicalLevel.@comment:
Hierarchical position of the described materials relative to other material from the same source.
This could be better specified (SES)

bf:organization.@comment: Manner in which the resource is divided into smaller units.

bf:pattern.@comment: Pattern of arrangement of materials within a unit.

@documentation.@description: Proportional relationship between an image's width and its height.
Resources expressed in an audible form, including music or other sounds.
Number assigned by publishers of sound recordings to identify the issue designation, or serial identification, of the resource.
Identifier assigned to the smallest identifiable unit of a recording session, e.g., a specific recording of an individual song.
Optical machine-readable representation of data relating to the item to which it is attached.
Underlying physical material of a resource.
Result of folding a printed sheet to form a gathering of leaves.
System used to format a video resource for television broadcast, e.g., HDTV, PAL.
Information about place and date associated with the capture (i.e., recording, filming, etc.) of the content of a resource.
Categorization reflecting the format of the storage medium and housing of a carrier.
Content that represents the whole or part of the earth, any celestial body, or imaginary place at any scale.

bf:projection.@comment: Method or system used to represent the surface of the earth or of a celestial sphere on a plane.

bf:ascensionAndDeclination.@comment: System for identifying the location of a celestial object in the sky covered by the cartographic content of a resource using the angles of right ascension and declination.

bf:coordinates.@comment: Mathematical system for identifying the area covered by the cartographic content of a resource, expressed either by means of longitude and latitude on the surface of planets or by the angles of right ascension and declination for celestial cartographic content.

bf:equinox.@comment:
One of two points of intersection of the ecliptic and the celestial equator, occupied by the sun when its declination is 0 degrees.
Sounds like this could be an object property with a class with two values? (SES)

bf:exclusionGRing.@comment: Coordinate pairs that identify the closed non-intersecting boundary of the area contained within the G-polygon outer ring that is excluded.

bf:outerGRing.@comment: Coordinate pairs that identify the closed non-intersecting boundary of the area covered.
bf:outerGRing.@label: Cartographic outer G ring area covered

@documentation.@description: Data type for encoding of geospatial information in a cartographic resource, e.g., raster, vector, point.
Object type for encoding of geospatial information in a cartographic resource, e.g., point, line, polygon.
Resource that shows spatial information, including maps, atlases, globes, digital, and other cartographic resources.
Dates associated with issues or items held.
System of coding and organizing materials according to their subject.

bf:classificationPortion.@comment: Classification number (single class number or beginning number of a span) that indicates the subject by applying a formal system of coding and organizing resources.

bf:edition.@comment:
Edition of the classification scheme, such as full, abridged or a number, when a classification scheme designates editions.
This could be an object property, with a range that is enumerated

bf:itemPortion.@comment: Number attached to a classification string that indicates a particular item.

bf:schedulePart.@comment: Designates whether the classification number is from the standard or optional part of a schedule or table.

bf:spanEnd.@comment: Ending number of classification number span.

bf:table.@comment: Number of the table from which the classification number in a subdivision entry is taken, e.g., a DDC table.

bf:tableSeq.@comment: Sequence number or other identifier for an internal classification sub arrangement or add in a classification scheme.

@documentation.@description: Dewey Decimal Classification number used for subject access.
Library of Congress Classification number used for subject access.
National Library of Medicine Classification number used for subject access
Universal Decimal Classification number used for subject access.
Identifier for scientific and technical periodical titles assigned by the International CODEN Section of Chemical Abstracts Service.
Aggregation of resources, generally gathered together artificially.
Title for a compilation of resources.
Color characteristics of a resource, e.g., black and white, multicolored, etc.
Categorization reflecting the fundamental form of communication in which the content is expressed and the human sense through which it is intended to be perceived.
Information that assists those with a sensory impairment for greater understanding of content, e.g., captions.
Agent and role with respect to the resource being described.

bf:agent.@comment: Entity associated with a resource or element of description, such as the name of the entity responsible for the content or of the publication, printing, distribution, issue, release or production of a resource.

bf:role.@comment: Function provided by a contributor, e.g., author, illustrator, etc.

@documentation.@description: Identifier assigned to a copyright registration or legal deposit.
Copyright or Legal Deposit registration information
Cover illustration of a resource.

Data encoded in a defined structure. Includes numeric data, environmental data,etc., used by applications software to calculate averages, correlations, etc., or to produce models, etc., but not normally displayed in its raw form.
Indication of specific types of reviews that have been carried out on the description information.
Rules used for the descriptive content of the resource description.
Technical specification relating to the digital encoding of text, image, audio, video, and other types of data in a resource.
Information about a work presented as part of the formal requirements for an academic degree.

bf:degree.@comment: Degree for which author was a candidate.

@documentation.@description: Identifier assigned to a thesis or dissertation for identification purposes .
Information relating to distribution of a resource.
Digital Object Identifier.
International Article Identifier.
Resource that is intended for manipulation by a computer, accessed either directly or remotely.
Suspension of light-sensitive chemicals used as a coating on a microfilm or microfiche, e.g., silver halide.
Speed at which streaming audio, video, etc., is designed to play, e.g., 32 kbps.
Schema, standard, etc., used to encode the digital content of a resource, e.g., MP3, XML, JPEG.
Numbering or other enumeration associated with issues or items held.
Numbering or other enumeration and dates associated with issues or items held.
Something that happens at a certain time and location, such as a performance, speech, or athletic event, that is documented by a resource.

bf:eventContent.@comment:
Work whose content is the described event.
This isn't be  a sub-property of relatedTo (SES)

@documentation.@description: Number and type of units and/or subunits making up a resource.
Two or more persons related by birth, marriage, adoption, civil union, or similar legal status, or who otherwise present themselves as a family.
Number of bytes in a digital file, e.g., 162 KB.
General type of data content encoded in a computer file, e.g., text file, audio file.
Identifier that is used to assist in the identification of antiquarian books by recording information comprising groups of characters taken from specified positions on specified pages of the book.
Size of the type used to represent the characters and symbols in a resource.
Information about intervals at which the parts of a serially produced resource or the updates to an integrating resource are issued.
Relationship between an original carrier and the carrier of a reproduction made from the original.
Indication of the program or process used to generate the description by application of a particular transformation.

Characteristics of works with similar plots, themes, settings, etc. (e.g., westerns, thrillers), or with a particular format of purpose (e.g., animation, short), or a combination (e.g., horror film where horror is the genre and film is the form).
Geographic coverage of the content of the resource.
Groove width of an analog disc or the groove pitch of an analog cylinder, e.g., coarse groove, microgroove
14 digit number assigned to identify trade items as various packaging levels. GTIN-14 encompasses EAN/UCC-128 and ITF-14.
Unique and persistent identifier for digital objects developed by the Corporation for National Research Initiatives.
Token or name that is associated with a resource, such as a URI or an ISBN.
Information about content intended to illustrate a resource.
Information about the circumstances, e.g., source, date, method, under which the resource was directly acquired.
Resource reflecting an individual, material embodiment of a Work.

bf:appliedMaterial.@comment: Physical or chemical substance applied to a base material of a resource.

bf:baseMaterial.@comment: Underlying physical material of a resource.

bf:bookFormat.@comment: Result of folding a printed sheet to form a gathering of leaves.

bf:carrier.@comment: Categorization reflecting the format of the storage medium and housing of a carrier.

bf:digitalCharacteristic.@comment: Technical specification relating to the digital encoding of text, image, audio, video, and other types of data in a resource.

bf:emulsion.@comment: Suspension of light-sensitive chemicals used as a coating on a microfilm or microfiche, e.g., silver halide.

bf:extent.@comment: Number and type of units and/or subunits making up a resource.

bf:fontSize.@comment: Size of the type used to represent the characters and symbols in a resource.

bf:generation.@comment: Relationship between an original carrier and the carrier of a reproduction made from the original.

bf:hasItem.@comment: Item which is an example of the described Instance.

bf:instanceOf.@comment: Work the Instance described instantiates or manifests. For use to connect Instances to Works in the BIBFRAME structure.

bf:issuedWith.@comment: Resource that is issued on the same carrier as the resource being described.

bf:layout.@comment: Arrangement of text, images, tactile notation, etc., in a resource.

bf:mount.@comment: Physical material used for the support or backing to which the base material of a resource has been attached.

bf:otherPhysicalFormat.@comment: Resource that is manifested in another physical carrier.

bf:polarity.@comment: Relationship of the colors and tones in an image to the colors and tones of the object reproduced.

bf:productionMethod.@comment: Process used to produce a resource.

bf:projectionCharacteristic.@comment: Technical specification relating to the projection of a motion picture film.

bf:provisionActivity.@comment: Place, name, and/or date information relating to the publication, printing, distribution, issue, release, production, etc. of a resource.

bf:reductionRatio.@comment: Size of a micro-image in relation to the original from which it was produced.

bf:reproductionOf.@comment: Resource that is a reproduction of another Resource.

bf:soundCharacteristic.@comment: Technical specification relating to the encoding of sound in a resource.

bf:systemRequirement.@comment: Equipment or system requirement beyond what is normal and obvious for the type of carrier or type of file, such as make and model of equipment or hardware, operating system, amount of memory, programming language, other necessary software, any plug-ins or peripherals required to play, view, or run the resource, etc.

bf:videoCharacteristic.@comment: Technical specification relating to the encoding of video images in a resource

bf:dimensions.@comment: Measurements of the carrier or carriers and/or the container of a resource.

bf:editionEnumeration.@comment: Enumeration of the edition; usually transcribed.

bf:editionStatement.@comment: Information identifying the edition or version of the resource and associated statements of responsibility for the edition; usually transcribed.

bf:provisionActivityStatement.@comment: Statement relating to providers of a resource; usually transcribed.

bf:responsibilityStatement.@comment: Statement relating to any persons, families, or corporate bodies responsible for the creation of, or contributing to the content of a resource; usually transcribed.

bf:seriesEnumeration.@comment: Series enumeration of the resource; usually transcribed.

bf:seriesStatement.@comment: Statement of the series the resource is in; usually transcribed; includes the ISSN if applicable.

bf:subseriesEnumeration.@comment: Subseries enumeration of the resource; usually transcribed.

bf:subseriesStatement.@comment: Statement of the subseries the resource is in; usually transcribed; includes the ISSN if applicable.

@documentation.@description: Information that identifies the specific intended or target audience or intellectual level for which the content described is considered appropriate. Also used to record interest and motivation levels and special learner characteristics.
International Standard Audiovisual Number.
International Standard Book Number.
International Standard Music Number.
International Standard Name Identifier, a unique, persistent reference number for the identities of contributors to creative works.
International Organization for Standardization standard number.
International Standard Recording Code.
International Standard Serial Number.
International Standard Serial Number that links together various media versions of a continuing resource.
Information about whether a resource is issued in one or more parts, the way it is updated, and its intended termination.
International Standard Text Code, a numbering system developed to enable the unique identification of textual works.
International Standard Musical Work Code, a unique, persistent reference number for the identification of musical works.
Single example of an Instance.

bf:electronicLocator.@comment:
Electronic location from which the resource is available.
This should be a data property of type xsd:anyURI (SES)

bf:enumerationOrChronology.@comment: Numbering and dates of issues or items held.
bf:enumerationOrChronology.@label: Numbering or other enumeration and dates associated with issues or items held.

bf:heldBy.@comment: Entity holding the item or from which it is available.

bf:immediateAcquisition.@comment: Information about the circumstances, e.g., source, date, method, under which the resource was directly acquired.

bf:itemOf.@comment: Instance for which the described Item is an example.

bf:shelfMark.@comment: Piece identifier, such as a call or other type of number.

bf:sublocation.@comment: Specific place within the holding entity where the item is located or made available.

bf:physicalLocation.@comment: Location in the holding agency where the item is shelved or stored.

@documentation.@description: Legal or political unit administering a geographic area.
Unique title for a continuing resource that is assigned by the ISSN International Center in conjunction with an ISSN.
Language entity.
Arrangement of text, images, tactile notation, etc., in a resource.
Identification number assigned by the Library of Congress to works acquired through one of its collaborative overseas acquisition programs.
Library of Congress Control Number that identifies a resource description.
Identifier established locally and not a standard number.
Information relating to manufacture of a resource.
Resource that is written in handwriting or typescript. These are generally unique resources.
Matrix identifier assigned to the master from which a specific sound recording was pressed.
Categorization reflecting the general type of intermediation device required to view, play, run, etc., the content of a resource.
Gathering of individuals or representatives of various bodies for the purpose of discussing and/or acting on topics of common interest.

Resource comprised of multiple types which are not driven by software. This may include materials in two or more forms that are related by virtue of their having been accumulated by or about a person or body., archival fonds.
Physical material used for the support or backing to which the base material of a resource has been attached.
Information on the symbol system used to convey the content of a movement resource.
Images intended to be perceived as moving, including motion pictures (using liveaction and/or animation), video recordings of performances, events,etc.

Electronic resource that is a computer program (i.e., digitally encoded instructions intended to be processed and performed by a computer) or which consists of multiple media types that are software driven, such as videogames.
Identifier appearing on a resource assigned by a distributor to a specific audio recording, notated music publication, music-related publication, or videorecording.
Ensemble for which a musical work is appropriate.

bf:ensembleType.@comment:
Specific type of ensemble, such as orchestra, band, guitar ensemble.
This is the sort of property that should be an *Objec*t property, with a range Class that has   Orchestra, band, etc, as Individuals. (SES)

@documentation.@description: Layout for content of a resource that is presented in the form of musical notation.
Instrument for which a musical work is appropriate.

bf:instrumentalType.@comment: Specific role of instrument, such as alternate, doubling, solo, ensemble.

@documentation.@description: Summary statement of the medium for a musical work.
Information on the symbol system used to convey the content of a music resource.

Identifiers assigned by a music publisher or printer to the printing plates for the notated portion of a notated music publication, or an identifier that emulates the printing plate tradition in contemporary publications.
Identifier assigned to a notated music publication other than an issue, matrix, or plate number.
Voice for which a musical work is appropriate.

bf:voiceType.@comment: Specific type of voice group, such as chorus, solo.

@documentation.@description: National Bibliography Number that identifies a resource description.
Graphic, non-realized representations of movement intended to be perceived visually, e.g. dance.
Graphic, non-realized representations of musical works intended to be perceived visually.
Information on the alphabet, script, or symbol system used to convey the content of the resource, including specialized scripts, typefaces, tactile notation, movement notation, and musical notation.
Information, usually in textual form, on attributes of a resource or some aspect of a resource.

bf:noteType.@comment:
Type of note.
Why is the type of note not a type? (SES)

@documentation.@description: Resource in a form intended to be perceived visually in three-dimensions. Includes man-made objects such as models, sculptures, clothing, and toys, as well as naturally occurring objects such as specimens mounted for viewing.
Number of objects in encoded geospatial information in a cartographic resource.
Corporation or group of persons and/or organizations that acts, or may act, as a unit.
Title in another language and/or script.
Individual or identity established by an individual (either alone or in collaboration with one or more other individuals).
Geographic location.
Configuration/number of sound channels used to make a recording, such as one channel for a monophonic recording, e.g., mono, stereo, quadraphonic, surround.
Equalization system, noise reduction system, etc., used in making an audio recording, e.g., CCIR standard, CX encoded, Dolby.
Speed at which an audio carrier must be operated to produce the sound intended, e.g., 78 rpm, 19 cm/s.
Relationship of the colors and tones in an image to the colors and tones of the object reproduced.
Number assigned to a publication for which the specified postal service permits the use of a special mailing class privilege.
Format used in the production of a projected image, e.g., Cinerama, IMAX.
Resource that is printed.
